chunk_content: Safe shelter-related repair or construction ✓ 231 APPENDIX E: GLOBAL OVC GRADUATION BENCHMARKS MATRIX GLOBAL ORPHANS AND VULNERABLE CHILDREN A P GRADUATION BENCHMARKS MATRIX P Updated July 6, 2018. Reviewed August 2023. E N This document provides information on the minimum global benchmarks for OVC graduation. Benchmarks are organized by D domain (healthy, stable, safe, and schooled) and key objective. I C E “Graduation” occurs when a child and caregiver enrolled in a PEPFAR OVC program are deemed to have become more stable S and no longer in need of OVC project-provided services. For caregivers and children 17 or under4 to be counted as graduated, all child and all caregiver beneficiaries in a household must meet ALL applicable (age and HIV status specific) graduation benchmarks established by PEPFAR for improving stability. Additional guidance and tools to facilitate implementation of these global minimum benchmarks is forthcoming. 1.
